<HTMLInputElementSize>
<summary>
The <strong><c>size</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLInputElement"/> interface defines the number of visible characters displayed. It reflects the {{htmlelement("input")}} element's <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#size"><c>size</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>The <c>size</c> property is relevant to the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/text"><c>text</c></see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/search"><c>search</c></see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/tel"><c>tel</c></see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/email"><c>email</c></see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/url"><c>url</c></see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input/password"><c>password</c></see> input type only. The value is a non-negative integer greater than zero. If omitted or invalid, the value is <c>20</c>.</para>
<para>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.MinLength"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLInputElement.MaxLength"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSelectElement.Size"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLInputElement/size"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>An integer.</value>
</HTMLInputElementSize>
